This Report Field will aggregate the values at a Pay component level from all Pay Calculation Related Calculations(PCRC) where Add / Subtract are selected in the dropdown Result Line.
 
On each PCRC, you have Add/Subtract option to indicate if the hours on Pay Calculation Related Calculations(PCRC) should be added to or subtracted from the Result Line Hours
 
Example # 1:
 
Pay Component : Base Pay
PCRC: Base Pay   Hours(Unprorated) = 40.00  Add option is selected
PCRC: Base Pay   Unpaid Hours = 8.00  Subtract Option is Selected
PCRC: Base Pay  Rate = 10.00  blank (do not select this for a non-hours related PCRC)
 
Result Line Hours = 32.00
 
Example # 2:
 
Pay Component : Overtime
PCRC: Overtime  Hours(Prorated) = 8.00  Add option is selected
PCRC: Overtime  Rate = 10.00 blank (do not select this for a non-hours related PCRC)
 
Result Line Hours = 8.00
 
 
Example # 3:
 
Pay Component : Unpaid Vacation
PCRC: Overtime  Hours(Prorated) = 4.00  Subtract option is selected
PCRC: Overtime  Rate = 10.00  blank (do not select this for a non-hours related PCRC)
 
Result Line Hours = 4.00
Pay component related calculation hours will be calculated on the reports for Business Object Payroll Result Line if not blank

This CRF returns the normalized numerical rating value from the overall rating of a manager's evaluation for the current performance review for the worker. The current review is determined by the field "Review Templates Used in Performance Over Time Report Field" configured on the "Maintain Employee Review Setup" task. This field defines a set of review templates, which are then ordered by the event completion date, with the most recently completed one defined as the current review. It is also important to note that the ratings are normalized using the rating scale specified in field Reporting Target Rating Scale configured on the same "Maintain Employee Review Setup" task.
The review rating for the project plan task for the worker.  Note that the value returned is based on the current project review rating scale in the tenant setup.

This CRF returns the normalized numerical rating value from the overall rating of a manager's evaluation for the 2nd previous performance review for the worker. The 2nd previous review is determined by the field "Review Templates Used in Performance Over Time Report Field" configured on the "Maintain Employee Review Setup" task. This field defines a set of review templates, which are then ordered by the event completion date, with the third most recently completed one defined as the 2nd previous review. It is also important to note that the ratings are normalized using the rating scale specified in field Reporting Target Rating Scale configured on the same "Maintain Employee Review Setup" task.

This field defines a set of review templates, which are then ordered by the event completion date, with the second most recently completed one defined as the previous review.
